(Link: https://simonwillison.net/2026/Apr/24/honker/#atom-everything) Tj
T*
(russellromney/honker "Postgres NOTIFY/LISTEN semantics" for SQLite, implemented as a Rust) Tj
T*
(SQLite extension and various language bindings to help make use of it. The design of this looks) Tj
T*
(very solid. It lets you write Python code for queues that looks like this: import honker db =) Tj
T*
(honker . open \( "app.db" \) emails = db . queue \( "emails" \) emails . enqueue \({ "to" :) Tj
T*
("alice@example.com" }\) # Consume \(in a worker process\) async for job in emails . claim \() Tj
T*
("worker-1" \): send \( job . payload \) job . ack \(\) And Kafka-style durable streams like this:) Tj
T*
(stream = db . stream \( "user-events" \) with db . transaction \(\) as tx : tx . execute \( "UPDATE) Tj
T*
(users SET name=? WHERE id=?" , [ name , uid ]\) stream . publish \({ "user_id" : uid , "change" :) Tj
T*
("name" }, tx = tx \) async for event in stream . subscribe \( consumer = "dashboard" \): await) Tj
T*
(push_to_browser \( event \) It also adds 20+ custom SQL functions including these two: SELECT) Tj
T*
(notify\( ' orders ' , ' {"id":42} ' \); SELECT honker_stream_read_since\( ' orders ' , 0 , 1000 \);) Tj
T*
(The extension requires WAL mode, and workers can poll the .db-wal file with a stat call every) Tj
T*
(1ms to get as close to real-time as possible without the expense of running a full SQ...) Tj
T*
() Tj
